\begin_inset Formula $T\left(e_{i,j},t\right)\subset\left(\cap_{k\in\mathcal{K}\backslash\left\{ i,j\right\} }\omega_{k}\left(t\right)\right)$
\end_inset

.
 We conclude that 
\begin_inset Formula $T\left(e_{i,j},t\right)\subset e_{i,j}\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $y\in e_{i,j}\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $y=\lambda z_{v}\left(t\right)+\left(1-\lambda\right)z_{w}\left(t\right)$
